The paper discusses a method for evaluating the quality of publishing venues in Computer Science based on paper publication data. This involves regression analysis and targeting metrics of interest. The paper also discusses how these venue scores can be used to evaluate individual academic authors and institutions. Given this focus on data analysis and evaluation, the most likely sub-categories are those related to data analysis and information retrieval (cs.DL, cs.IR), as well as those related to databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
